post_text: We have an amazing staff at Kingston Community Schools. Please take a moment to visit Knights Insurance Agency Facebook page and share an amazing story about one of our staff members.
shared_text:
Knights Insurance Agency is with Hunter Caister and 4 others.
August 19 at 10:00 AM ·

In continuing with our "Spreading Kindness Like Confetti" campaign, we wanted to show some kindness to our teachers as well. So we've put together a gift basket for two hardworking educators, one for Cass City and one for Kingston. Drop a kind note or story about a current teacher from either school who has shown kindness to you, your child, or the community as a whole. Each comment will qualify them for an entry into our basket drawing. You may nominate more than one teacher. Please include which school they are from in your comment. All nominations must be accompanied by a story or a kind message about that teacher to be entered into the drawing. Nominations close at 12 pm on 8/24/2020. Random drawings will be selected by Mason Brown, 8th grader at Cass City and Brantley Boggs, 2nd grader at Kingston. Please share this post so that as many teachers as possible get nominated! NOMINATIONS MUST BE SUBMITTED ON THE ORIGINAL POST ON THE KNIGHTS INSURANCE PAGE

Hello Kingston Schools Community,

We are working hard on preparing for all of the different scenarios for the start of school. We want to provide our students and families with the best possible options for their specific comfort level. One of the EO requirements that will be enforced starting Monday is that all adults including staff must fill out the COVID 19 health screener on line before entering the buildings. You can capture the form using a phone/camera or a QR reader app. Students are exempt from completing the screener.

Here is an update on the High School (Public) Library:

1. The library will reopen June 9. Summer hours 10-3. Curbside only.
Pick up requests in the front parking lot. Place all returns in the drop box. Call 989-683-2500 for more information. No donations yet. Looking forward to serving the community physically again.
2. Any students who still have library items checked out please return in the drop box at the front of the library. Remember the library is late fee fine free. You will only be charged for the cost of any item still out once school starts back up.

Thanks,

Glenna Ford
Librarian

Dear Kingston Families

I would like to encourage you to be watching your mailbox for information on the newly approved Pandemic EBT Program. Because Kingston Community School District is a CEP district (where our entire district receives free breakfast and lunch), every child that is registered with our district will receive these benefits. Should you have any further questions concerning eligibility and/or card information, please reference the FAQ sheet linked below. **Please note that these benefits are in ADDITION to the meals that the school currently provides on Tuesday's.

post_text:
What: Community Discussion and Input on a potential multipurpose baseball/softball/track/band facility

When: Tomorrow (Wednesday) at 7pm

Where: HS cafeteria

Who: Anyone who would like to share their ideas, opinions.

Why: We would like to preserve our brand new HS gym and Weight rooms, both places have been used for Spring and Winter batting and pitching practice.

post_text:
Note to Visitors to Kingston Jr./Sr. High regarding the new secure entry. Student and staff safety is our number one priority. To that end part of the bond project was to move office staff and add locking doors at the second level of entry to provide a true “secure entry”. That system is in place and it has caused some confusion to guests to our building.

Office staff have three options. 1.) To buzz guests into the entry way. 2.) To buzz guests thought the second level of doors into the main hallway to report to the old office where all student business is conducted. Ie students sign in and sign out, dropping off of money, food, homework, gym clothes etc. Option 3. To buzz entry through the new door to the new office.

Unknown guests and infrequent visitors will be required to enter through the new office for a face to face with office staff.
